  "prompt": "What is months at level in Accenture?",
  "response": "\"Months at level\" in Accenture refers to the amount of time an employee has spent in their current role or position level within the company. At Accenture, as in many other consulting firms, employees typically progress through a series of predefined roles or levels, often based on experience, performance, and time spent at each level. Tracking the \"months at level\" helps in assessing an employee's readiness for promotion or for taking on more responsibilities. It's a standard metric used to manage career progression and development plans within the organization.",
